  <div class="copy">
  Nintendo has flirted with free-to-play game ideas over the past few years ‚Äî inventively with titles like Rusty's Real Deal Baseball and more conventionally with demos like Wii Sports Club for Wii U ‚Äî but nothing the company has done is as typically free-to-play as Pok√©mon Shuffle, a new puzzle game from The Pok√©mon Company and Genus Sonority.
Pok√©mon Shuffle for Nintendo 3DS hit the Nintendo eShop this week as a free download. It's a gem-matching puzzle game, like Genus Sonority's Pok√©mon Trozei for Nintendo DS though it plays very differently. Players can match three or more Pokemon heads in a row on the 3DS' bottom screen and successful matches will inflict damage on a¬†Pok√©mon¬†on the top screen. Line up Pokemon, create chains and combos, and you'll defeat (and then hopefully capture)...
