  <div class="copy">
  Klaus Teuber's hit board game The Settlers of Catan is being adapted for film and television, according to an announcement from producer Gail Katz, who has locked down international rights to the property.
Katz has served as producer or executive producer on a number of films and television series, including Air Force One, The Perfect Storm, The Agency and Cashmere Mafia. Her latest project is Pawn Sacrifice, a Cold War-era biographical film about¬†chess players Bobby Fischer and Boris Spassky ‚Äî arguably a board game-based film as well.
Based on comments from Katz, it sounds like The Settlers of Catan ‚Äî which is pretty light on story and focuses on strategically building out settlements ‚Äî will be used as a "starting point" for a more robust story.
