    <div class="block block_e left article" data-entry-id="7834628">
  <header>
      <h6><a href="http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.polygon.com&#x2F;news">News</a></h6>
      <a href="http://www.polygon.com/2015/2/19/8070587/not-a-hero-release-date#comments" class="comment_count">4 Comments</a>
  </header>

  <div class="pinned_wrapper">
    <div class="block_body">
        <a class="block_img vox-lazy-load" data-analytics-link="article:image" data-imgkey="45727278:cinema:1" data-original="https://cdn3.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/H4AyBuJMfkASY0mM2-yz8GPLQgk=/0x0:1920x1080/640x360/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/45727278/ss_b2a538bf3a46676eb867534baf33a8caea3894ff.1920x1080.0.0.jpg" data-ratio="1.7777777777777777" href="http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.polygon.com&#x2F;2015&#x2F;2&#x2F;19&#x2F;8070587&#x2F;not-a-hero-release-date"></a>

<div class="meta">
  <h2><a href="http:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.polygon.com&#x2F;2015&#x2F;2&#x2F;19&#x2F;8070587&#x2F;not-a-hero-release-date" data-analytics-link="article">Vote BunnyLord May 7 when Not a Hero arrives on&nbsp;PC</a></h2>
  <p class="byline">
      By <a href="http://www.polygon.com/users/davetach">Dave Tach</a>
  <span class="long_date">
      at 1:00p
  </span>
  <span class="short_date">
    02.19.15
  </span>
  <span class="m-entry-admin-button " data-remote-admin-entry-type="button" data-remote-admin-entry-id="7834628"></span>

</p>

  
  <div class="copy">
  Not a Hero, developer Roll7's retro-styled cover-based shooter, will arrive on Steam, GOG and the Humble Store for Linux, Mac and Windows PC on May 7, the developer and publisher Devolver Digital announced today.
"The Roll7 team really wanted to embrace the indie developer lifestyle by delaying the release of Not A Hero on several occasions for no discernible reason," creative director John Ribbins said. "Unfortunately, we also have a publisher so we have to stop messing around and release it. So, May 7 I guess."
For more on Not a Hero, in which a talking rabbit and aspiring mayor called BunnyLord tasks his campaign manager, Steve, with cleaning up a city's underworld to recruit voters,  be sure to read our impressions and watch the Overview video below.

</div>

</div>

